## 6. Kubelet Manager Wiring — The `isImmutable` Closures

### ConfigMap

**`kubernetes--v1.32.0` → `pkg/kubelet/configmap/configmap_manager.go`** (lines 148–157)

```go
isImmutable := func(object runtime.Object) bool {
    if configMap, ok := object.(*v1.ConfigMap); ok {
        return configMap.Immutable != nil && *configMap.Immutable
    }
    return false
}
gr := corev1.Resource("configmap")
return &configMapManager{
    manager: manager.NewWatchBasedManager(listConfigMap, watchConfigMap, newConfigMap, isImmutable, gr, resyncInterval, getConfigMapNames),
}
```

### Secret

**`kubernetes--v1.32.0` → `pkg/kubelet/secret/secret_manager.go`** (lines 149–158)

```go
isImmutable := func(object runtime.Object) bool {
    if secret, ok := object.(*v1.Secret); ok {
        return secret.Immutable != nil && *secret.Immutable
    }
    return false
}
gr := corev1.Resource("secret")
return &secretManager{
    manager: manager.NewWatchBasedManager(listSecret, watchSecret, newSecret, isImmutable, gr, resyncInterval, getSecretNames),
}
```

Both closures use the same nil-safe double-dereference pattern: `Immutable != nil && *Immutable`. This correctly handles the three-valued semantics of `*bool` — `nil` (unset/mutable), `false` (explicitly mutable), and `true` (immutable).

