## 9. Tests

### Integration Test — Immutable Secret with Empty Data Values

**`kubernetes--v1.32.0` → `test/integration/secrets/secrets_test.go`**

`DoTestSecretsImmutableWithEmptyValue` (lines 60–105) tests a subtle edge case: a secret with `Immutable: true` and a data value of `{}` (empty byte slice). It verifies that a strategic-merge patch that preserves the same data is accepted — this guards against a regression where the server incorrectly treated `[]byte{}` and `nil` as different values, which would have caused all patches to immutable secrets with empty values to be rejected.

### Integration Test — Watch Manager

**`kubernetes--v1.32.0` → `test/integration/kubelet/watch_manager_test.go`** (lines 64–70)

```go
// We want all watches to be up and running to stress test it.
// So don't treat any secret as immutable here.
isImmutable := func(_ runtime.Object) bool { return false }
store := manager.NewObjectCache(listObj, watchObj, newObj, isImmutable, ...)
```

This test explicitly passes `isImmutable = always false` to stress-test the watch manager under load without the optimization interfering.

### E2E Conformance Tests

**`kubernetes--v1.32.0` → `test/e2e/common/storage/configmap_volume.go`** (lines 495–553)  
**`kubernetes--v1.32.0` → `test/e2e/common/storage/secrets_volume.go`** (lines 377–435)

Both are tagged `framework.ConformanceIt` (meaning they are part of the Kubernetes conformance test suite). They exercise the complete lifecycle against a live API server:

| Step | Expected result |
|---|---|
| Create object, update `data` | ✅ Succeeds |
| Set `Immutable: true` | ✅ Succeeds |
| Update `data` | ❌ `apierrors.IsInvalid` |
| Set `Immutable: false` | ❌ `apierrors.IsInvalid` |
| Update `metadata.labels` | ✅ Succeeds |
| Delete the object | ✅ Succeeds |

